President Muhammadu Buhari is in a virtual meeting with members of the Governors Forum’s Security Committee. The committee is headed by Kogi Governor, Yahaya Bello. NAN reports that the meeting will discuss Nigeria’s security situation. In attendance are Vice President Yemi Osinbajo; Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha; Chief of Staff to the President, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, and Chief of Defence Staff, Gabriel Olonisakin. Others are Chief of Naval Staff, Ibok Ekwe Ibas; Inspector-General of Police, Muhammed Adamu; Chief of Air Staff, Sadique Abubakar; Director-General, National Intelligence Agency, Ahmed Rufa’i and the Director-General, Department of State Services, Yusuf Bichi. Chief of Army Staff, Lt.-Gen. Tukur Buratai is represented by Maj-Gen. U. S. Yakubu. Also present are Governors of Bayelsa – Douye Diri; Borno – Babagana Zulum; Ebonyi – David Umahi; Lagos – Babajide Sanwo-Olu.